items.title: Awesome Game Engine Dev
items.content_text:
### Game Engines / Awesome Collections

*   üìö [CoolEngines (‚≠ê88)](https://github.com/JohnClarking/CoolEngines) - List of open source graphic & game engines.

### Libraries / C++

*   C++: Physics
    *   üéâ [Box2D (‚≠ê8.9k)](https://github.com/erincatto/box2d) - Battle tested 2D physics for games. \[[Docs](https://box2d.org/documentation/) | [Fixed Time-Step](https://www.unagames.com/blog/daniele/2010/06/fixed-time-step-implementation-box2d) | [Tutorials](http://www.iforce2d.net/b2dtut/introduction)]
    *   üéâ [Bullet Physics (‚≠ê14k)](https://github.com/bulletphysics/bullet3) - Popular 3D physics libary.
    *   üéâ [Chrono (‚≠ê2.5k)](https://github.com/projectchrono/chrono) - High-performance multiphysics and multibody dynamics simulations. \[[Gallery](https://projectchrono.org/gallery/)]
    *   üéâ [Edyn (‚≠ê703)](https://github.com/xissburg/edyn) - Multi-threaded, networked physics engine. Supports large dynamic worlds. \[[Testbed (‚≠ê39)](https://github.com/xissburg/edyn-testbed)]
    *   üéâ [Jolt Physics (‚≠ê8.1k)](https://github.com/jrouwe/JoltPhysics) - Multi-core friendly rigid body 3D physics and collision detection.
    *   üéâ [Liquid Fun (‚≠ê4.8k)](https://github.com/google/liquidfun) - Extension of *Box2D*, adds particle-based fluid and soft bodies. \[[Demos](http://google.github.io/liquidfun/)]
    *   üéâ [Newton Dynamics (‚≠ê990)](https://github.com/MADEAPPS/newton-dynamics/) - Real-time simulation of 3D environments.
    *   üéâ [ODE](http://www.ode.org/) - Open Dynamics Engine, 3D rigid body physics.
    *   üéâ [Qu3e (‚≠ê958)](https://github.com/RandyGaul/qu3e) - Fast 3D physics engine, created to be used in games.
    *   üéâ [ReactPhysics3D (‚≠ê1.6k)](https://github.com/DanielChappuis/reactphysics3d) - 3D physics engine.
    *   üéâ [Slingshot (‚≠ê130)](https://github.com/Slingshot-Physics/slingshot-community) - Constraint-based physics engine for 3D rigid body dynamics.

items.title: Awesome Zsh Plugins
items.content_text:
### Plugins / [superconsole](https://github.com/alexchmykhalo/superconsole) - Windows-only

*   [delete-prompt (‚≠ê5)](https://github.com/aoyama-val/zsh-delete-prompt) - ZSH widget to delete the prompt texts within the current line. It is useful when executing pasted commands from the web or a README. A leading non-alphanumeric character + space is detected as a prompt.
*   [exa (zap-zsh) (‚≠ê20)](https://github.com/zap-zsh/exa) - Overrides common commands to use exa instead.
*   [exa-ls (zpm-zsh) (‚≠ê100)](https://github.com/zpm-zsh/ls) - Zsh plugin for ls.
*   [eza (twopizza9621536) (‚≠ê5)](https://github.com/twopizza9621536/zsh-eza) - Replaces `ls` with [eza-community/eza (‚≠ê16k)](https://github.com/eza-community/eza).
*   [no-ps2 (‚≠ê23)](https://github.com/romkatv/zsh-no-ps2) - When this plugin is used, Enter inserts a newline if the typed command is incomplete. No PS2!
*   [run-scripts (‚≠ê5)](https://github.com/Aireck2/zsh-run-scripts) - Runs scripts from `package.json`.

### Completions / [superconsole](https://github.com/alexchmykhalo/superconsole) - Windows-only

*   [inshellisense (‚≠ê9.4k)](https://github.com/microsoft/inshellisense) - Provides IDE style autocomplete for shells. It's a terminal native runtime for autocomplete which has support for 600+ command line tools. inshellisense supports `bash`, `fish`, `zsh` and `pwsh` on the Windows, Linux, & MacOS operating systems.

items.content_html:
Plugins / superconsole - Windows-only

  • delete-prompt (‚≠ê5) - ZSH widget to delete the prompt texts within the current line. It is useful when executing pasted commands from the web or a README. A leading non-alphanumeric character + space is detected as a prompt.
  • exa (zap-zsh) (‚≠ê20) - Overrides common commands to use exa instead.
  • exa-ls (zpm-zsh) (‚≠ê100) - Zsh plugin for ls.
  • eza (twopizza9621536) (‚≠ê5) - Replaces ls with eza-community/eza (‚≠ê16k).
  • no-ps2 (‚≠ê23) - When this plugin is used, Enter inserts a newline if the typed command is incomplete. No PS2!
  • run-scripts (‚≠ê5) - Runs scripts from package.json.
